<h1>AnswerNest Community Guidelines</h1>
<p class="intro">
    Welcome to <strong>AnswerNest</strong>. This platform is built for people to ask questions,
    share knowledge, and help others. To keep the community helpful and respectful,
    all users must follow these guidelines.
</p>

<hr>

<section>
    <h2>1. Ask Clear Questions</h2>
    <p>
        When asking a question, explain your problem clearly so others can understand it easily.
        Include useful details such as:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>What problem you are facing</li>
        <li>What you already tried</li>
        <li>Expected result</li>
        <li>Actual error or issue</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>2. Use a Proper Title</h2>
    <p>
        Your title should summarize your question. A good title helps others quickly
        understand the topic of your question.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Bad: "Help my code not working"</li>
        <li>Good: "How to connect Node.js with MySQL using mysql2?"</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>3. Provide Enough Details</h2>
    <p>
        Use the description area to explain your question fully.
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Include code snippets</li>
        <li>Add error messages</li>
        <li>Explain steps that cause the problem</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>4. Search Before Asking</h2>
    <p>
        Before posting a new question, try searching on AnswerNest.
        Someone may have already asked the same question and received a helpful answer.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>5. Write Helpful Answers</h2>
    <p>
        When answering questions, try to provide clear explanations and useful solutions.
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Explain the solution step-by-step</li>
        <li>Provide examples or code snippets</li>
        <li>Share helpful resources if needed</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>6. Stay On Topic</h2>
    <p>
        Answers and comments should stay related to the original question.
        Avoid posting unrelated discussions or spam content.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>7. Be Respectful</h2>
    <p>
        AnswerNest is a respectful community. Harassment, hate speech,
        and abusive language are not allowed.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>8. No Spam or Promotion</h2>
    <p>
        Do not use AnswerNest for advertising or repeated promotion of products
        or services.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>9. No Illegal Content</h2>
    <p>
        Content related to illegal activities, pirated software, or harmful instructions
        is not allowed and may be removed.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>10. Moderation</h2>
    <p>
        Moderators may edit or remove posts that violate the guidelines to maintain
        the quality of the community.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>11. Account Responsibility</h2>
    <p>
        Users are responsible for keeping their accounts secure. Do not share your
        login information with others.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>12. Reporting Issues</h2>
    <p>
        If you see content that violates these guidelines, please report it so
        moderators can review it.
    </p>
</section>
```

